GLOBAL
Currency: gold only; no barter standard between cities; exchange rates
for foreign goods priced in gold at point of sale
Guild pricing: licensed guilds post tariffs; unlicensed sellers may be
cheaper but have no recourse mechanism if goods are faulty
Caravan routes: posted departure times at major gates; adventurer escorts
hired at guardhouses; raider activity reported on route-boards
Route intelligence is a commodity; fresh reports of road conditions and
bandit activity are sold at inn common rooms and post offices
Roc Road dual jurisdiction: Midgaard holds legal charter authority; Kiess
convoy marshals control actual throughput; every checkpoint is a friction
point where both claim authority and neither fully yields
Saltglass Reach has three routes: Swift Line (light cargo, strict
documentation), Heavy Road (bulk goods, slow but legally airtight), Sealed
Route (relic/funerary, armed escort required, most expensive)
~
MIDGAARD
Guild Concordat sets minimum prices and quality standards; disputes go to
the Ledgerhouse for arbitration
Three founding trade blocs: River Factors (barge trade), Upland Syndicate
(ore/timber), Temple Compact (pilgrim arbitration); all still influence
pricing in their sectors
Lantern Registry posts official tariffs; discrepancies from posted rates
are a recoverable civil offense
Barge grain arrives from northern routes; upland ore from western corridors;
pilgrim goods from all directions; Midgaard's margin comes from the junction
Roc Road goods carry dual-seal documentation from Midgaard wardens and Kiess
convoy marshals; which seal is authoritative in disputes is contested
Lantern Road through the Great Northern Forest is the northern grain and timber
artery; Ashfang warband disruptions raise Midgaard prices within days
Night of First Lamps and Day of Open Ledgers are peak trading days; official
tariff schedules reset — check before committing to long contracts
~
KOWLOON
Harbor Syndics license all dock trade; their inspectors in blue sashes audit
every cargo manifest before it crosses the threshold
Jade Magistracy handles emergency rationing and can override market pricing
during flood or famine declarations — invoke carefully
Night markets (violet-marked) operate outside standard guild oversight;
prices are negotiable but provenance documentation is sparse
River Corsairs under Blacktide Shen disrupt northern supply runs; reports
of their movements worth coin at the Warden of Iron's office
Southern Grain Compact with Rakuen: reserve-release dispatched within two
weeks of formal emergency declaration; activated four times in sixty years
Ledger Day (midsummer): Jade Magistracy opens accounts for public audit; peak
period for commercial intelligence — pricing and supply disputes surface
~
KIESS
Trade Syndics coordinate caravan contracts along Roc Road; their annex
manages all commercial flow between Midgaard and the western frontier
Tariff-sharing negotiations with Kowloon ongoing via Midgaard relay corridor;
rates may shift; check the Syndics' current posted schedule
Evermeet's collapse disrupted established trade credit chains; Kiess rebuilt
from cash-basis; most transactions here are pay-now, no credit extended
Roc Road: Midgaard road wardens hold legal seals; Kiess convoy marshals
control throughput; independent wayfolk run ferries and repairs at every
point neither city covers; handoff disputes are common
Relic market: Evermeet excavations and Roc Road salvage produce contested-
provenance items; authentication at the Trade Syndics' Annex recommended
before paying relic prices; Conclave-marked items are legally complex
~
RAKUEN
Garden Ledger tracks all surplus allocation; ask a Ledger Clerk before
purchasing bulk goods — some commodities are rationed
Kowloon sends grain; Kiess sends clerks; Midgaard sends subsidies but not
recognition; this shapes what's available and at what price
Common orchards and waterworks are maintained communally; attempting to
purchase exclusive access is a serious social offense
Bloom Council rotating stewardship means trade partners change; establish
relationships with the Ledger Clerks, who are the institutional continuity
Eccentric Woodland path-guide services are Rakuen's primary service export;
guides hold territorial knowledge no map provides; pricing is high and non-
negotiable — they know there is no alternative route
Abundance-sharing expectation: community pricing for basics; charging market
rates for essential goods requires public justification before the Ledger
Clerks; creates friction for outside merchants but is strictly enforced
~
MAFDET
Dual attestation required on all cargo: both inland and maritime legal
standards verified; adds cost but prevents legal liability at destination
Shoreward House provides bilingual clerks for oasis/maritime contract
notation differences; essential for first-time inland traders
Sand-Sea Carters' Guild controls overland Saltglass Reach transit; Guild
contracts are non-negotiable on route and timing
First Claw oaths bind permanently; breaking one means exclusion from the
entire Mafdet trade network, not just the immediate counterparty
Saltglass Reach routes: Swift Line (light/high-value cargo, minimal assay,
extreme documentation), Heavy Road (bulk goods, triple-assessed at cairns,
slow), Sealed Route (relic/funerary, armed escort, most legally secure)
Storm Ledger issues weather advisories based on accumulated observational
records; captains who ignore them lose bonded cargo insurance; consult before
departure
~
